{
  "video_id": "jOsX_HnJtHU",
  "title": "A new way to think about the transition to motherhood | Alexandra Sacks",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13309.0,
      "end_time": 17239.0,
      "text": "Do you remember a time when you felt hormonal and moody?"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 17263.0,
      "end_time": 19247.0,
      "text": "Your skin was breaking out,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 19271.0,
      "end_time": 23373.0,
      "text": "your body was growing in strange places and very fast,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 24235.0,
      "end_time": 25392.0,
      "text": "and at the same time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 25416.0,
      "end_time": 28375.0,
      "text": "people were expecting you to be grown-up in this new way."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 29960.0,
      "end_time": 30407.0,
      "text": "Teenagers, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 31344.0,
      "end_time": 36155.0,
      "text": "Well, these same changes happen to a woman when she&#39;s having a baby."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 36179.0,
      "end_time": 40533.0,
      "text": "And we know that it&#39;s normal for teenagers to feel all over the place,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 40557.0,
      "end_time": 43912.0,
      "text": "so why don&#39;t we talk about pregnancy in the same way?"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 44850.0,
      "end_time": 50503.0,
      "text": "There are entire textbooks written about the developmental arc of adolescence,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 50527.0,
      "end_time": 54738.0,
      "text": "and we don&#39;t even have a word to describe the transition to motherhood."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 55271.0,
      "end_time": 56436.0,
      "text": "We need one."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 57272.0,
      "end_time": 60501.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m a psychiatrist who works with pregnant and postpartum women,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 60526.0,
      "end_time": 62182.0,
      "text": "a reproductive psychiatrist,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 62206.0,
      "end_time": 65124.0,
      "text": "and in the decade that I&#39;ve been working in this field,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 65147.00000000001,
      "end_time": 66868.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve noticed a pattern."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 66892.0,
      "end_time": 68848.0,
      "text": "It goes something like this:"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 68872.0,
      "end_time": 70330.0,
      "text": "a woman calls me up,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 70354.0,
      "end_time": 72350.0,
      "text": "she&#39;s just had a baby,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 72590.0,
      "end_time": 73497.0,
      "text": "and she&#39;s concerned."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 73521.0,
      "end_time": 77956.0,
      "text": "She says, \"I&#39;m not good at this. I&#39;m not enjoying this."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 77980.0,
      "end_time": 80186.0,
      "text": "Do I have postpartum depression?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 80615.0,
      "end_time": 82979.0,
      "text": "So I go through the symptoms of that diagnosis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 83400.0,
      "end_time": 85993.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s clear to me that she&#39;s not clinically depressed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 86170.0,
      "end_time": 87497.0,
      "text": "and I tell her that."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 87521.0,
      "end_time": 89414.0,
      "text": "But she isn&#39;t reassured."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 89438.0,
      "end_time": 92593.0,
      "text": "\"It isn&#39;t supposed to feel like this,\" she insists."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 92617.0,
      "end_time": 95909.0,
      "text": "So I say, \"OK. What did you expect it to feel like?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 96495.0,
      "end_time": 101152.0,
      "text": "She says, \"I thought motherhood would make feel whole and happy."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 101708.0,
      "end_time": 105135.0,
      "text": "I thought my instincts would naturally tell me what to do."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 105606.0,
      "end_time": 108533.0,
      "text": "I thought I&#39;d always want to put the baby first.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 109463.0,
      "end_time": 113583.0,
      "text": "This -- this is an unrealistic expectation"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 113608.0,
      "end_time": 116119.0,
      "text": "of what the transition to motherhood feels like."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 116636.0,
      "end_time": 118684.0,
      "text": "And it wasn&#39;t just her."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 118708.0,
      "end_time": 123663.0,
      "text": "I was getting calls with questions like this from hundreds of women,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 123687.0,
      "end_time": 126337.0,
      "text": "all concerned that something was wrong,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 126361.0,
      "end_time": 128393.0,
      "text": "because they couldn&#39;t measure up."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 128955.00000000001,
      "end_time": 131291.0,
      "text": "And I didn&#39;t know how to help them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 131315.0,
      "end_time": 133925.0,
      "text": "because telling them that they weren&#39;t sick"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 133949.0,
      "end_time": 135785.0,
      "text": "wasn&#39;t making them feel better."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 136841.0,
      "end_time": 141122.0,
      "text": "I wanted to find a way to normalize this transition,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 141145.0,
      "end_time": 146548.0,
      "text": "to explain that discomfort is not always the same thing as disease."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 146572.0,
      "end_time": 150630.0,
      "text": "So I set out to learn more about the psychology of motherhood."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 150654.0,
      "end_time": 153528.0,
      "text": "But there actually wasn&#39;t much in the medical textbooks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 153552.0,
      "end_time": 156168.0,
      "text": "because doctors mostly write about disease."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 156725.0,
      "end_time": 158557.0,
      "text": "So I turned to anthropology."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 159148.0,
      "end_time": 162594.0,
      "text": "And it took me two years, but in an out-of-print essay"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 162618.0,
      "end_time": 166588.0,
      "text": "written in 1973 by Dana Raphael,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 166612.0,
      "end_time": 171115.0,
      "text": "I finally found a helpful way to frame this conversation:"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 171139.0,
      "end_time": 172581.0,
      "text": "matrescence."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 173672.0,
      "end_time": 178484.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s not a coincidence that \"matrescence\" sounds like \"adolescence.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 179174.0,
      "end_time": 182866.0,
      "text": "Both are times when body morphing and hormone shifting"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 182890.0,
      "end_time": 186594.0,
      "text": "lead to an upheaval in how a person feels emotionally"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 186618.0,
      "end_time": 188867.0,
      "text": "and how they fit into the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 188891.0,
      "end_time": 193490.0,
      "text": "And like adolescence, matrescence is not a disease,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 193740.0,
      "end_time": 195896.0,
      "text": "but since it&#39;s not in the medical vocabulary,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 195920.0,
      "end_time": 198607.0,
      "text": "since doctors aren&#39;t educating people about it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 198631.0,
      "end_time": 201420.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s being confused with a more serious condition"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 201444.0,
      "end_time": 203209.0,
      "text": "called postpartum depression."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 204444.0,
      "end_time": 206932.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve been building on the anthropology literature"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 206956.0,
      "end_time": 210950.0,
      "text": "and have been talking about matrescence with my patients"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 210120.0,
      "end_time": 212710.0,
      "text": "using a concept called the \"push and pull.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 213730.0,
      "end_time": 214497.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s the pull part."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 215670.0,
      "end_time": 219388.0,
      "text": "As humans, our babies are uniquely dependent."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 219412.0,
      "end_time": 222355.0,
      "text": "Unlike other animals, our babies can&#39;t walk,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 222379.0,
      "end_time": 223965.0,
      "text": "they can&#39;t feed themselves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 223990.0,
      "end_time": 225873.0,
      "text": "they&#39;re very hard to take care of."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 225897.0,
      "end_time": 230769.0,
      "text": "So evolution has helped us out with this hormone called oxytocin."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 230794.0,
      "end_time": 233950.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s released around childbirth"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 233119.0,
      "end_time": 235595.0,
      "text": "and also during skin-to-skin touch,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 235619.0,
      "end_time": 238890.0,
      "text": "so it rises even if you didn&#39;t give birth to the baby."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 239668.0,
      "end_time": 245137.0,
      "text": "Oxytocin helps a human mother&#39;s brain zoom in, pulling her attention in,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 245161.0,
      "end_time": 247997.0,
      "text": "so that the baby is now at the center of her world."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 248567.0,
      "end_time": 253949.0,
      "text": "But at the same time, her mind is pushing away,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 253973.0,
      "end_time": 258609.0,
      "text": "because she remembers there are all these other parts to her identity --"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 259434.00000000003,
      "end_time": 260989.00000000003,
      "text": "other relationships,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 261529.0,
      "end_time": 262835.0,
      "text": "her work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 262859.0,
      "end_time": 264111.0,
      "text": "hobbies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 264135.0,
      "end_time": 266662.0,
      "text": "a spiritual and intellectual life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 266686.0,
      "end_time": 268953.0,
      "text": "not to mention physical needs:"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 268978.0,
      "end_time": 272341.0,
      "text": "to sleep, to eat, to exercise,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 272366.0,
      "end_time": 273837.0,
      "text": "to have sex,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 273861.0,
      "end_time": 275275.0,
      "text": "to go to the bathroom,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 275299.0,
      "end_time": 276467.0,
      "text": "alone --"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 276491.0,
      "end_time": 277659.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 277684.0,
      "end_time": 278854.0,
      "text": "if possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 279727.0,
      "end_time": 283760.0,
      "text": "This is the emotional tug-of-war of matrescence."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 284150.0,
      "end_time": 287565.0,
      "text": "This is the tension the women calling me were feeling."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 287589.0,
      "end_time": 289869.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s why they thought they were sick."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 291200.0,
      "end_time": 295960.0,
      "text": "If women understood the natural progression of matrescence,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 295985.0,
      "end_time": 301628.0,
      "text": "if they knew that most people found it hard to live inside this push and pull,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 301652.0,
      "end_time": 304577.0,
      "text": "if they knew that under these circumstances,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 304601.0,
      "end_time": 309151.0,
      "text": "ambivalence was normal and nothing to be ashamed of,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 309175.0,
      "end_time": 311205.0,
      "text": "they would feel less alone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 311229.0,
      "end_time": 313532.0,
      "text": "they would feel less stigmatized,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 313556.0,
      "end_time": 317681.0,
      "text": "and I think it would even reduce rates of postpartum depression."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 318332.0,
      "end_time": 320276.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d love to study that one day."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 321451.0,
      "end_time": 323299.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m a believer in talk therapy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 323323.0,
      "end_time": 326152.0,
      "text": "so if we&#39;re going to change the way our culture understands"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 326176.0,
      "end_time": 327969.0,
      "text": "this transition to motherhood,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 327994.0,
      "end_time": 330158.0,
      "text": "women need to be talking to each other,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 330182.0,
      "end_time": 331504.0,
      "text": "not just me."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 332313.0,
      "end_time": 335942.0,
      "text": "So mothers, talk about your matrescence"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 335966.0,
      "end_time": 338613.0,
      "text": "with other mothers, with your friends,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 338637.0,
      "end_time": 340866.0,
      "text": "and, if you have one, with your partner,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 340890.0,
      "end_time": 343777.0,
      "text": "so that they can understand their own transition"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 343801.0,
      "end_time": 345426.0,
      "text": "and better support you."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 345891.0,
      "end_time": 348942.0,
      "text": "But it&#39;s not just about protecting your relationship."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 349534.0,
      "end_time": 352979.0,
      "text": "When you preserve a separate part of your identity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 353300.0,
      "end_time": 356919.0,
      "text": "you&#39;re also leaving room for your child to develop their own."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 358295.0,
      "end_time": 362145.0,
      "text": "When a baby is born, so is a mother,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 362169.0,
      "end_time": 364978.0,
      "text": "each unsteady in their own way."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 365659.0,
      "end_time": 367896.0,
      "text": "Matrescence is profound,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 367920.0,
      "end_time": 369688.0,
      "text": "but it&#39;s also hard,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 369712.0,
      "end_time": 371563.0,
      "text": "and that&#39;s what makes it human."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 372120.0,
      "end_time": 373167.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 373191.0,
      "end_time": 374960.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}